      "instruction": "<p>Once browned, remove the pork from the dish and set aside on a clean plate</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to the dish with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong> and <strong>crushed garlic</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, give everything a good mix up and place the dish in the oven for an initial 20 min – these are your <strong>smoky potatoes</strong></p>",
